"title": "5078: Abraham, significance of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5078",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Whereas Jews see Abraham as the father of their nation on account of God's covenant with him, Christians see Abraham as the father of all who believe in Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>The significance of Abraham for nations other than Israel</h2>\n<h3>Abraham was the father of many nations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:3-Gen17:6\">GEN 17:3–17:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:20\">GEN 17:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:1-Gen25:4\">GEN 25:1–25:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:12-Gen25:18\">GEN 25:12–25:18</a> <em>Muslim Arabs trace their ancestry through Ishmael to Abraham.</em></p>\n<h3>Abraham was to be a means of blessing to many nations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:3\">GEN 12:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:18\">GEN 18:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen22:17-Gen22:18\">GEN 22:17–22:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:25\">ACT 3:25</a></p>\n<h2>The significance of Abraham for the people of Israel</h2>\n<h3>Israel traces its origins back to God's call of Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:1-Gen12:2\">GEN 12:1–12:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:2-Josh24:3\">JOS 24:2–24:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:2-Acts7:3\">ACT 7:2–7:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:8-Heb11:10\">HEB 11:8–11:10</a></p>\n<h3>God promises the land of Canaan to Abraham's descendants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:7-Neh9:8\">NEH 9:7–9:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:1-Gen15:21\">GEN 15:1–15:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:1-Gen17:8\">GEN 17:1–17:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:8\">EXO 6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:5\">DEU 9:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:4-Acts7:5\">ACT 7:4–7:5</a></p>\n<h3>God is subsequently known in Israel as the God of Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:36\">1KI 18:36</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:26-Gen24:27\">GEN 24:26–24:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:24\">GEN 26:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:53\">GEN 31:53</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:9\">PSA 47:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:32\">ACT 7:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:6\">EXO 3:6</a></p>\n<h3>Abraham is seen as the father of the Jewish nation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:39\">JHN 8:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:5-Ps105:6\">PSA 105:5–105:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:8\">ISA 41:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:1-Isa51:2\">ISA 51:1–51:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:54-Luke1:55\">LUK 1:54–1:55</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:33\">JHN 8:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:26\">ACT 13:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:1\">ROM 11:1</a></p>\n<h3>God deals with Israel on the basis of his covenant with Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:14-1Chr16:18\">1CH 16:14–16:18</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:7-Ps105:11\">PSA 105:7–105:11</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:23-Exod2:25\">EXO 2:23–2:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:22-2Kgs13:23\">2KI 13:22–13:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:42-Ps105:45\">PSA 105:42–105:45</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:68-Luke1:75\">LUK 1:68–1:75</a></p>\n<h3>Circumcision was the sign of participation in God's covenant with Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:9-Gen17:14\">GEN 17:9–17:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:3\">LEV 12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:22\">JHN 7:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:1\">ACT 15:1</a></p>\n<h2>The significance of Abraham for Christians</h2>\n<h3>Abraham was an ancestor of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:1\">MAT 1:1</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:34\">LUK 3:34</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ attacks Jewish confidence in mere physical descent from Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:9-Matt3:10\">MAT 3:9–3:10</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:8-Luke3:9\">LUK 3:8–3:9</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:33-John8:41\">JHN 8:33–8:41</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ makes a point of identifying outcasts as children of Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:7-Luke19:9\">LUK 19:7–19:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:10-Luke13:16\">LUK 13:10–13:16</a></p>\n<h3>God's promise to Abraham is not inherited by those who obey the law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:15-Gal3:18\">GAL 3:15–3:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:13-Rom4:16\">ROM 4:13–4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:21-Gal4:31\">GAL 4:21–4:31</a></p>\n<h3>God's promise to Abraham is fulfilled in Jesus Christ, who is Abraham's seed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:16\">GAL 3:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:7\">GEN 12:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:15\">GEN 13:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:7\">GEN 24:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:19\">GAL 3:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:29\">GAL 3:29</a></p>\n<h3>Abraham is the father of those who are justified by faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:6-Gal3:9\">GAL 3:6–3:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:6\">GEN 15:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:1-Rom4:25\">ROM 4:1–4:25</a></p>\n<h3>Abraham's obedience to God shows that faith must lead to good works</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:20-Jas2:24\">JAS 2:20–2:24</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Fellowship with Abraham is a symbol of salvation</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:11-Matt8:12\">MAT 8:11–8:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:28-Luke13:29\">LUK 13:28–13:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:19-Luke16:26\">LUK 16:19–16:26</a></p>",
